NAME
       write - write to a file descriptor

SYNOPSIS
       #include <unistd.h>

       ssize_t write(int fd, const void *buf, size_t count);

DESCRIPTION
       Writes up to count bytes from buf to fd. For block devices the
       offset advances; for terminals the bytes are passed straight to
       the framebuffer renderer and to /dev/ttyS0.

RETURN VALUE
       Bytes successfully written, or -1 on error.

ERRORS
       EBADF      fd is not open for writing
       EFAULT     buf is not a valid pointer

SEE ALSO
       read(2), open(2)
